 Suitcase' made the band look even more like Nirvana copyists to their
 critics as they opted to record with Steve Albini (he had recorded
 Nirvana's last album 1993's 'In Utero'), and 1999's 'The Science Of
 Things' merely emphasised the fact that when it comes to tuneful misery,
 Bush have got that vital commercial pop touch.

