@node "DANZIG"

 DANZIG

 Originally the frontman for cartoon gore-hounds the @{"Misfits" link "MISFITS"} (the same lot
 that so influenced @{"Metallica" link "METALLICA"} in their early years), Glenn Danzig had first
 spent some time as the force behind Samhain before launching his own
 eponymous rock band. Eschewing the schlocky hardcore noise of his
 formative years, Danzig instead opted for a more basic blues thunder,
 and with his muscular frame and rich crooning vocals came across very much
 as a kind of demonic Elvis figure, both on stage and on record. With a band
 consisting of Eerie Von (bass), John Christ (guitar) and Chuck Biscuits
 (drums), Danzig created the dark menace of his self-titled debut album,
 a cross between gothic horror and hard-rocking blues. Refining the Satanic
 horror schtick for album number two, 'Danzig II: Lucifuge', it was finally
 with 'Danzing III: How The Gods Kill' that all the elements of melody,
 primal power and raw emotion finally coalesced in a truly satisfactory way.
 Subsequent releases - 'Danzig IV', 'Danzig 5: Blackacidevil' and 'Danzig
 6:66 Satan's Child' - have found him moving towards more of
 a spine-tingling industrial sound to complement his icy blues howl.
 A chillingly influential and uncompromising artist.

 Recommended listening: 'Danzig'

