@node "DEFTONES"

 DEFTONES

 Formed back in the early '90s and signed to Madonna's Maverick label
 through Warners, California's Deftones were one of the major acts
 pioneering a style that has subsequently been dubbed nu-metal.
 Essentially championing a downtuned, angsty brand of rock, Chino Moreno
 (vocals), Stephen Carpenter (guitar), Chi Cheng (bass) and Abe Cunningham
 (drums) also had the sense and style to throw in elements of hip-hop, punk
 and hardcore to create a truly unique sound which was not only extremely
 heavy, but also highly accessible. Their debut album, 1995's 'Adrenaline',
 was very aptly titled and contained blast after blast of carefully honed
 noise. Their obvious proficiency in the studio was enhanced by a reputation
 for enormously energetic live shows, with singer Moreno literally throwing
 himself bodily into each performance with such fearless abandon he was in
 danger of serious injury virtually on a nightly basis. Subsequent album
 'Around The Fur' proved to be yet another smash with fans and found the
 band gaining serious exposure through the release of the single 'My Own
 Summer (Shove It)'.

 Recommended listening: 'Around The Fur'

 ZUBi's recommended listening: 'Adrenaline'

