 GWAR

 The direct, but undeniably bastard, offspring of the school of shock rock
 pioneered by the likes of Alice Cooper, GWAR - allegedly short for God What
 A Racket - are actually a sick joke perpetrated by a bunch of American art
 students. They claim to be a clan of interplanetary warriors descended from
 aliens trapped in Antarctica and their mission on earth is to sexually
 enslave its inhabitants. Well, something like that anyway. The upshot of
 all this conceptual nonsense is some ridiculously over-the-top metal
 contained on several albums rejoicing under such titles as 'Scumdogs Of
 The Unuverse', 'America Must Be Destroyed', 'This Toilet Earth' and
 'We Kill Everything'. This racket would be as nothing, however, were it
 not for the exuberant carnival of bad taste the band indulge in while on
 stage. The individual members enjoy such absurd names as Oderus Urungus,
 Balsac The Jaws Of Death, Slymenstra Hymen and The Sexecutioner.
 And there's at least another four, all of them performing the most
 heinously twisted rock theatrics to complement the obviously deranged
 tunes. Dressed in alien barbarian costumes that would make Manowar think
 twice about where some of the spikes might end up by accident, they gleeful
 chuck around copious quantities of stage blood, luminous green semen and
 a variety severed limbs while bashing through their mutant metal.
 Unsurprisingly these antics have succeeded in getting them banned from
 venues all around the globe.

 Recommended listening: Scumdogs Of The Universe

