@node "KID ROCK"

 KID ROCK

 One of the few truly pioneering artists to fuse rap and rock in a
 convincing manner, Kid Rock (aka Bob Ritchie) grew up in the small town
 of Romeo, Michigan, a suburb of the sprawling Detroit metropolis.
 During the early 80s the Kid was a veritable musical magpie absorbing
 every style of music that inspired him from Johnny Cash, to @{"Lynyrd Skynyrd" link "LYNYRD SKYNYRD"},
 to the pumping beats of Run DMC. This totally natural synthesis of diverse
 influences - and an unequivocal love of the rap star's hedonistic life
 style - inspired the Kid to spin the wheels of steel himself. The result
 was 1990's 'Grits Sandwiches For Breakfast' and a controversial hit in
 'Yodelling In The Valley'. The first of many expletive-fuelled raps,
 the oral sex subject matter and accompanying swearfest was just too much
 for the broadcast regulation authorities and a local radio station was
 slapped with a huge fine for playing it. There is, naturally, no better
 form of publicity and the Kid returned with two more sinfully exuberant
 albums packed with metallic rip offs and stolen samples - 'The Polyfuze
 Method' (1993) and 'Early Mornin' Stoned Pimp' (1996). The Kid was a bad
 to the bone, foul-mouthed, skirt-chasing exhibitionist and he didn't care
 who knew it. With this successful fusion of styles came his biggest hit
 yet, the breakthrough 'Devil Without A Cause'. The metal was potent and
 the raps eye-wateringly perverse, and just to deliver this with no small
 degree of authenticity the Kid put together his own group - the Twisted
 Brown Trucker Band - to bring a truly live KO punch to the sound.

 Recommended listening: 'Devil Without A Cause'

