@node "MARILYN MANSON"

 MARILYN MANSON

 @{"Alice Cooper" link "ALICE COOPER"} may have pioneered the whole shock rock movement in the 70s,
 but for the MTV-dependent 90s and the new millennium Marilyn Manson (aka
 Brian Warner) is definitely the icon of choice among discerning metal fans
 keen to upset their parents and teachers. Warner's career actually started
 out in the realms of music journalism which doubtless gave him the
 incentive to launch his career as the androgynous gothic freak nightmare
 of Marilyn Manson. Starting out as Marilyn Manson And The Spooky Kids,
 before becoming simply Marilyn Manson, the band rapidly formed something
 of a major reputation in their home locale of south Florida,
 the conservative nature of the area highlighting their deliberate mission
 to offend any self-appointed moral guardians. Winning a supporting slot
 with @{"Nine Inch Nails" link "NINE INCH NAILS"} the band signed to Trent Reznor's Nothing Records,
 the perfect home for their sub-industrial glam grind. Their 1994 debut
 'Portrait Of An American Family' was a solid enough stab at skewering the
 values of middle America but with 1996's 'Antichrist Superstar' and its
 slew of MTV hit singles - aided by some dazzling video work - Manson became
 public enemy number one. As if it were possible, 1998 follow-up 'Mechanical
 Animals' taunted the moral guardians with even more viciously acerbic
 satire.

 Recommended listening: 'Antichrist Superstar'

 ZUBi's recommended listening: AGREE

