@node "SKUNK ANANSIE"

 SKUNK ANANSIE

 Not many rock bands can claim to being successful when it comes to
 political polemic but London band Skunk Anansie can not only claim to be
 successful in that arena but also in terms of artistic creativity and
 commerciality. No mean feat for such a young band. Formed in 1994 by
 Skin (vocals), Ace (guitars), Cass (bass) and Robbie (drums) their
 confrontational style and street-level polemics dealing with everything
 from racism, to personal relationships, to the hypocrisies of organised
 religion landed them a record deal almost immediately. Key to the band's
 spiraling success was Skin's ability to inject virtually every syllable
 with either passion or rage or, most often, both. Not only that but the
 band could also switch into a softer more soulful mode when the mood
 suited them too. This artistic flexibility was very much to the fore with
 1995's debut, the staggeringly accomplished 'Sunburnt And Paranoid',
 a potent combination of sweet but barbed ballads such as 'Charity' and
 'Pity', along with more straight ahead rockers such as 'Selling Jesus
 Again'. Almost immediately the band made friends with the singles charts.
 Follow-ups 'Stoosh' and 'Post Orgasmic Chill' extended the band's obvious
 commercial aspects with yet another brace of powerful singles, but their
 obvious radio-friendly aspects were still acutely balanced against their
 more abrasive and uncompromising side.

 Recommended listening: 'Sunburnt And Paranoid'

