@node "SLIPKNOT"

 SLIPKNOT

 Up to now Des Moines, Iowa, couldn't really claim to be of any major
 significance in terms of rock and metal until the ear-bleeding tornado
 of noise that is Slipknot came into existence, that is. Back in 1995 the
 band's line-up was very fluid but it didn't take long for the current
 line-up to take shape. Everything about Slipknot is an attempt to pervert
 that natural balance of things, to upset and offend by deliberately not
 conforming to the norm. To this end the band settled on nine members -
 DJ Sid Wilson, drummer Joey Jordison, bassist Paul Gray, percussionist
 Chris Fehn, guitarist Jim Root, sampler Craig Jones, percussionist
 Shawn Crahan, guitarist Mick Thomson, and vocalist Corey Taylor -
 insisting that this was the optimum set-up for the Slipknot aural crusade.
 What's more they decided to wear boiler suits and each band member adopted
 a mask of their own choice to make themselves as anonymous as possible on
 stage, making the music the prime focus at all times. Of course, this
 visual aspect of the band would be meaningless were it not backed up by
 something truly incredible. Through their constant rehearsal and touring
 the Slipknot sound has developed into a full-blown tirade of hip hop, death
 metal, and rap, all of it brought into sharp focus through the tightly
 orchestrated percussive onslaught. Their self-released debut, 1996's 'Mate,
 Feed, Kill, Repeat', attracted the attention of thrash producer
 Ross Robinson and the result was their self-titled debut which has been
 astonishing metal fans (and pretty much everyone else!) the world over.
 Intense, bloody, rabid catharsis: Slipknot is all these things and more.

 Recommended listening: 'Slipknot'

