@node "SOULFLY"

 SOULFLY

 When the extraordinary happened with guitarist/vocalist Max Cavalera
 leaving @{"Sepultura" link "SEPULTURA"}, both his future and that of his former outfit looked
 extremely shaky indeed. Sepultura, of course, continued but not only did
 Max have to deal with losing touch with the band that he formed with his
 drummer brother Igor, he also had to come to terms with the murder of his
 stepson, Dana Wells. The only way to deal with the ensuing trauma and
 insecurity was to engross himself in music - hence the creation of Max's
 next project, Soulfly. Taking off where he had left Sepultura, the sound
 Max aimed for was just as heavy and just as tribal - capitalising on the
 traditional Brazilian instrumentation used on Sepultura's groundbreaking
 'Roots' album - but also included touches of experimentation hitherto
 unexplored. One particularly bruising song, 'Bumba', for instance,
 utilised samples and was co-produced by Mario Caldato Jr who had
 previously worked with the Beastie Boys. Elsewhere, Max roped in
 a plethora of contemporary metal stars - @{"Fear Factory" link "FEAR FACTORY"} chums Burton C Bell,
 Dino Cazares and Christian Olde Wolbers, @{"Limp Bizkit" link "LIMP BIZKIT"} dudes Fred Durst and
 DJ Lethal, @{"Deftones" link "DEFTONES"}' Chino Moreno, Dub War's Benji, and Cypress Hill's
 Eric Bobo - to create as awesome and expansive a sound as possible.
 An aim he has surely succeeded in fulfilling.

 Recommended listening: 'Soulfly'

