@node "SPINAL TAP"

 SPINAL TAP

 Formed in 1984 Spinal Tap were the evil brainchild of a group of sharp
 American satirists. Some would argue that the word of rock is quite capable
 of making fun of itself - often quite unintentionally - and doesn't need
 any help from a bunch of comedy actors. Nevertheless, the group were given
 a full history by their creators and Nigel Tufnell, David St Hubbins and
 Derek Smalls were the names of the prime movers in the band. First coming
 to prominence in the 1984 film This Is Spinal Tap, the world of rock gave
 the film ample scope to truly put the steel toe-capped boot into the
 excesses and egos associated with rock. The ageing and failing rock group
 were portrayed as washed up has-beens incapable of telling when their star
 has waned and the set pieces were so accurate that anyone who was unaware
 of the spoof actually thought they were watching a real documentary.
 Pushing the joke even further Spinal Tap also released 'Break Like The
 Wind' in 1992 and preceded its release with the single 'Bitch School'.
 The album and inevitable tour obviously could not match the brilliance
 of the movie but they had their moments. Since then the band have been
 wheeled out of mothballs whenever a suitable charity performance requires
 their appearance.

 Recommended viewing: 'This Is Spinal Tap'

