 VAN HALEN

 It's funny to think that this immensely successful hard rock band actually
 toyed with calling themselves Rat Salade back in their early days.
 The suggestion to name themselves after guitarist Eddie Van Halen came
 from singer @{"David Lee Roth" link "DAVID LEE ROTH"} and the combination of their complementing
 talents would take the band to the very pinnacle of success. When the band
 formed back in 1975 they were originally a covers band but soon developed
 a reputation as stars in the making with some inspired performances around
 the California club scene. Given a chance to shine in the studio by
 legendary hard rock producer Ted Templeman and the results were magical.
 Their 1978 self-titled debut was the very essence of vaudeville pizzazz
 (thanks to 'Diamond' Dave) and guitar heaven (thanks to Eddie's
 finger-flinging antics). 'Van Halen II', 'Women And Children First' and
 'Fair Warning', and '1984' were platinum-selling classics one and all,
 displaying an intuitive grasp of both melody and showmanship. And yet
 a band like Van Halen seemingly couldn't be home to two such monumental
 talents and Roth left the band to be replaced by @{"Sammy Hagar" link "SAMMY HAGAR"}. At first it
 seemed impossible for someone to replicate Roth's infectious sense of fun
 and limelight hogging ego, but Hagar brought different qualities to the
 role and still the platinum albums came. Until recently when Hagar was
 replaced by ex-@{"Extreme" link "EXTREME"} singer Gary Cherone and the results were very dull
 indeed. Latest news suggests that Roth and the Van Halen boys have kissed
 and made up and will be recording very soon.

