@node "VENOM"

 VENOM

 Whether you regard the Geordie metallers as the very musical incarnation
 of Satan on earth or just some sad cartoonish fools, you cannot deny the
 immense influence Cronos (bass/vocals), Mantas (guitar) and Abaddon exerted
 on the nascent black metal and thrash scenes. Formed in 1980 the band
 legendarily refused to support anyone and so their first gig was apparently
 a headlining slot at the Hammersmith Odeon back in June 1984! Whatever the
 facts are, however, it was with such intense live performances - huge
 quantities of pyrotechnics and a ridiculously loud sound system - that
 the band became immediately synonymous. Not only that, their records were
 equally brutal. 1981's 'Welcome To Hell' was an unsubtle blur of thrashing
 guitars, snarled vocals and tales of infernal damnation. Follow-up album,
 the appropriately titled 'Black Metal', however, is arguably the recording
 from which so many other bands would draw inspiration to explore the genre
 themselves. It was a diabolical masterpiece. 'At War With Satan' provided
 more of the same and then things started to go very wrong indeed with
 personality clashes being cited for the suddenly shifting line-up.
 Since then Venom have resolutely refused to die and continue to chuck out
 albums at varying intervals.

 Recommended listening: 'Black Metal'

